canonical:
  title: 誕日疏
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 覺鑑淵澄佛方便以應物主恩山重臣至誠而祝釐宜叩玄扃用資純嘏俱將庸陋端遇聖明値開國定社之時無能爲也承策勳報功之寵烏敢當哉徒罄有加之心每祝無疆之筭誕辰方届虔禱益深肆就精廬恭陳勝采香熏妙供法演眞宗營締雖微感通卽邇福如川至永孚于休壽與天齊俾昌而熾
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 誕日疏
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 覺鑑淵澄佛。方便以應物。主恩山重。臣至誠而祝釐。宜叩玄扃。用資純嘏。俱將庸陋。端遇聖明。値開國定社之時。無能爲也。承策勳報功之寵。烏敢當哉。徒罄有加之心。每祝無疆之筭。誕辰方届。虔禱益深。肆就精廬。恭陳勝采。香熏妙供。法演眞宗。營締雖微。感通卽邇。福如川至。永孚于休。壽與天齊。俾昌而熾。
korean:
  title: 탄일소
  author: 이첨
  language: kor
  text: 부처님의 지혜는 연못처럼 맑으므로, 방편(方便)으로 만물에 응하여 주시며, 임금님의 은덕은 산처럼 높으므로, 지성으로 복을 빕니다. 그러므로 현묘한 법문에 정성을 드려서, 순수한 복을 받도록 자뢰하나이다. 신은 용렬하고 고루한 바탕으로 성명(聖明)을 만나서, 국가를 열고 사직을 정할 때에, 아무것도 한 일이 없이 훈장을 책정하여 공을 주는 은총을 입었으니, 어찌 감당하겠나이까. 다만 정성을 다하여 만수무강하시기를 늘 축수할 뿐입니다. 이제 탄일을 맞이하여 성심껏 기도하는 마음이 더욱 간절하옵기에, 절에 나아가서 삼가 훌륭한 법식을 차립니다. 향은 신묘한 공양을 훈훈하게 하고, 법은 참된 종지를 연설하오니, 장만한 것은 빈약하오나 부처님께서 곧 감통하여 주셔서, 복이 냇물처럼 이르러 길이 아름다운 복을 누리고, 수명은 하늘과 더불어 가지런하여 더욱 창성하여지이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1140_010_0340&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Prayer on the Birthday
  author: Lee Cham
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The Buddha's wisdom gleams as clear as a still pond,
    manifesting through compassion to answer all things.
    The sovereign's grace towers high as mountains,
    and I, your servant, offer heartfelt prayers for blessings.

    Thus do I bow before the mystical gateway of dharma,
    seking to receive the pure grace that flows there.
    I, whose talents are meager and humble,
    have met this sage and enlightened age,
    this moment when nations are founded and states secured.
    Yet I have done nothing—what claim have I
    to the honors bestowed for merit and service?
    I dare not presume such rewards are mine.

    I can only exhaust the depths of my sincerity,
    endlessly praying for your boundless years.
    Now as your birthday arrives,
    my prayers grow ever more fervent.
    I proceed to this sacred sanctuary
    and humbly arrange the finest offerings.

    The incense perfumes the wondrous gifts,
    while the dharma expounds the true teachings.
    Though what I have gathered is humble and slight,
    the Buddha's response comes swift and near.
    Blessings flow like rivers unceasing,
    securing eternal grace and good fortune.
    May your years lengthen with heaven itself,
    growing ever more radiant and flourishing.
  footnotes:
    - This is a ceremonial prayer written to honor a ruler's birthday, blending Buddhist devotional language with Confucian expressions of loyalty and respect.
    - The poem employs traditional metaphors of water (ponds, rivers) for wisdom and grace, and mountains for the enduring nature of imperial virtue.
